This paper discusses the use of MontyLingua, an English text processor, in various research areas such as natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
